<subSubSection box="[543,1044,700,727]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="23.[543,1044,700,727]" box="[543,1044,700,727]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Snyder, 1954" authorityName="Snyder" authorityYear="1954" box="[673,1044,700,727]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Cyrtoneurininae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[673,882,700,726]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Cyrtoneurininae</emphasis>
Snyder, 1954
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[187,1398,765,863]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
This is essentially a Neotropical group extending into southern North America. It is rather heterogeneous and doubtfully monophyletic. Among the currently included 12 genera I have examined species from five of them (
<tableCitation box="[348,436,836,862]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="5.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetBox="[238,1379,394,1980]" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next 4 pages). Summary of vein C chaetotaxy with respect to multistate characterA for genus-group taxa of Fanniidae Schnabel &amp; Dziedcicki, 1911 and Muscidae Latreille, 1802. Examined genera highlighted in yellow. See ‘Material and methods’ for explanation of character states A0–8." pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Table 1</tableCitation>
). They all agree in having vein C extensively setulose ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1313,894,921]" box="[189,1313,894,921]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis box="[189,199,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Giglio-Tos, 1893" authorityName="Giglio-Tos" authorityYear="1893" box="[214,582,894,920]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cyrtoneurina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,372,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Cyrtoneurina</emphasis>
Giglio-Tos, 1893
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Malloch, 1925" authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1925" box="[594,955,894,921]" class="Insecta" family="Diptera" genus="Cyrtoneuropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[594,774,894,920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Cyrtoneuropsis</emphasis>
Malloch, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Townsend, 1919" authorityName="Townsend" authorityYear="1919" box="[967,1313,894,920]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Neomuscina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1112,895,920]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Neomuscina</emphasis>
Townsend, 1919
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,940,1038]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
The examined species of the above genera share the prevalent muscid state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1122,1158,940,966]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
A 
<quantity box="[1144,1158,940,966]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" unit="in" value="4.0">4</quantity>
</emphasis>
in which vein C is bare dorsally and extensively setulose ventrally: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Giglio-Tos" authorityYear="1893" box="[776,934,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cyrtoneurina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[776,934,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Cyrtoneurina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(2 spp indet.), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1925" box="[1120,1300,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Diptera" genus="Cyrtoneuropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1120,1300,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Cyrtoneuropsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(8 spp), 
<taxonomicName authority="Dodge, 1955" authorityName="Dodge" authorityYear="1955" box="[191,641,1011,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Neomuscina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufoscutella">
<emphasis box="[191,483,1011,1037]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Neomuscina rufoscutella</emphasis>
Dodge, 1955
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wulp, 1896" authorityName="Wulp" authorityYear="1896" box="[697,1009,1011,1037]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Neomuscina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tripunctata">
<emphasis box="[697,862,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">N. tripunctata</emphasis>
Wulp, 1896
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,568,1068,1095]" box="[189,568,1068,1095]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1069,1094]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque, 1954" authorityName="Albuquerque" authorityYear="1954" box="[213,568,1068,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Arthurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[213,334,1069,1095]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Arthurella</emphasis>
Albuquerque, 1954
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1115,1212]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
Among the two species examined, 
<taxonomicName authority="Albuquerque, 1954" authorityName="Albuquerque" authorityYear="1954" box="[627,1105,1115,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Arthurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nudiseta">
<emphasis box="[627,860,1115,1141]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Arthurella nudiseta</emphasis>
Albuquerque, 1954
</taxonomicName>
has vein C extensively setulose dorsally (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[466,501,1150,1176]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A8</emphasis>
), while 
<taxonomicName authority="Patitucci &amp; Mariluis" authorityName="Patitucci &amp; Mariluis" authorityYear="2011" box="[600,1000,1150,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Arthurella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choelensis">
<emphasis box="[600,617,1151,1177]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[632,754,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">choelensis</emphasis>
Patitucci &amp; Mariluis
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Patitucci L. D. &amp; Mariluis J. C. &amp; Aballay F. H." box="[1037,1274,1150,1177]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" pagination="56 - 62" refId="ref15383" refString="Patitucci L. D., Mariluis J. C. &amp; Aballay F. H. 2011. A new species of the South American genus Arthurella Albuquerque (Diptera: Muscidae), with a key to species and new records. Zootaxa 2810 (1): 56 - 62. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2810.1.6" type="journal article" year="2011">
Patitucci 
<emphasis box="[1145,1202,1150,1176]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">et al.</emphasis>
, 2011
</bibRefCitation>
is without dorsal setulae on CS1 (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[522,558,1185,1211]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A7</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,572,1243,1270]" box="[189,572,1243,1270]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis box="[189,199,1244,1269]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">•</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Snyder, 1949" authorityName="Snyder" authorityYear="1949" box="[214,572,1243,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pseudoptilolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[214,410,1243,1269]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">Pseudoptilolepis</emphasis>
Snyder, 1949
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1398,1290,1316]" box="[189,1398,1290,1316]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">
<heading box="[189,1398,1290,1316]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" reason="2">
The only examined species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Snyder, 1949" authorityName="Snyder" authorityYear="1949" box="[515,796,1290,1316]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Pseudoptilolepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusa">
<emphasis box="[515,634,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">P. confusa</emphasis>
Snyder, 1949
</taxonomicName>
, has vein C extensively setulose dorsally (state 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1344,1380,1290,1316]" pageId="23" pageNumber="117">A8</emphasis>
).
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
